@startuml e2e-04-quiz-fill-in
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
title E2E-04: Quiz Session — Fill-in Question (Hybrid Mode)

actor User
participant "CLI\nmain.py" as CLI
participant "QuizOrchestrator\nquiz.py" as QUIZ
participant "Retriever" as RET
participant "PTC\nptc.py" as PTC
participant "Router\nrouter.py" as ROUTER
participant "LocalAdapter\n(Ollama)" as LOCAL
participant "Scorer\nscorer.py" as SCORER
participant "SessionLog\nsession_log.py" as LOG

User -> CLI : python cli/main.py quiz --topic "SSDT"
CLI -> QUIZ : run_session(topic="SSDT", mode="hybrid")

note over QUIZ, LOG
  Retrieval + PTC phase identical to E2E-03.
  Shown from routing step onward.
end note

== Routing + Question Generation ==
QUIZ -> ROUTER : route("generate_question", "fill_in", "hybrid")
ROUTER --> QUIZ : "local"

QUIZ -> LOCAL : generate(question_prompt +\n  ptc_result.compressed_text)
LOCAL --> QUIZ : "The _____ table maps Windows\nsyscall numbers to kernel function addresses."

QUIZ --> User : Q: "The _____ table maps Windows\n    syscall numbers to kernel function addresses."

== User Answers ==
User -> CLI : types answer: "SSDT"
CLI -> QUIZ : user_answer = "SSDT"

== Routing + Answer Scoring ==
QUIZ -> ROUTER : route("score_answer", "fill_in", "hybrid")
ROUTER --> QUIZ : "local"

note right of QUIZ
  fill_in scoring uses difflib,
  not a model call — local means
  score_fill_in() is called directly.
end note

QUIZ -> SCORER : score_fill_in(user_answer="SSDT",\n               correct_answer="SSDT")
SCORER -> SCORER : user.lower() == correct.lower() → 1.0
SCORER --> QUIZ : Score(value=1.0, feedback="Correct!", correct_answer="SSDT")

== Logging ==
QUIZ -> LOG : append(QuestionLog(type="fill_in", score=1.0,\n              model_used="local", tokens_local=95,\n              tokens_premium=0, ...))
LOG -> LOG : flush to session_<timestamp>.json

QUIZ --> CLI : Score(1.0, feedback="Correct!", correct_answer="SSDT")
CLI --> User : Score: 1.0 — Correct!\nCorrect answer: SSDT\n\nNext question? (Y/N)

@enduml
